I feel like such an idiot.

I finally figured out why I’m so inconsistent at tournaments, despite feeling like I am skilled.

My general strategy usually revolves around making reads, and maximizing my advantage state and edge guards, with very little reactive play.

Oh…🫠 https://t.co/kB2BvbdOT4

When I do have the advantage I’m strong but because making reads is not going to work out every time, I take a lot of damage before I get that combo or edge guard.

Need to start focusing on being more reactive, and I’m sure I’ll be more consistent, and not have to rely on reads.

Making reads isn’t a bad thing, but it should be a thing you try a few times in a match when you feel it’s safe to do so, or as a last resort, it’s not something that should be your whole strategy.

I’ll work on it the best I can. I want to get better.
